1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Sensory hacks that actually work.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Number one.

3
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Keep noise-canceling headphones
in your bag at all times.

4
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Even without music, they cut
overwhelming sounds by 30%.

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Game changer for grocery stores.

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Number two.

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:20,000
Let your kid wear sunglasses indoors.

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Fluorescent lights are brutal
for sensory-sensitive kids.

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Who cares what people think?

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Number three.

11
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Rotate fidgets weekly.

12
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Kids get bored. The novelty
is what keeps them working.

13
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Number four.

14
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Chewing is calming.

15
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Chew necklaces, crunchy snacks,
thick smoothies through a straw.

16
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Offer them before the meltdown starts.

17
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Save this for later.

18
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Follow for more autism parenting tips.
